args:
With his power wrested away from him by
Beren, the Other is annihilated. Afterward,
Phares, the other Zethia, and Volk appear,
a discussion is had, and the party prepares
to do battle.
She is there upon the throne.
Zethia? Zethia, are you all right?!\nCome on, wake up!
Easy—she has simply lost consciousness.\nHer life is not in danger, and she should\nawaken after a short while.
But what happened to me?\nI thought Morsayati...
Turns out the little freak\nover there had other plans.
Beren? Brother? Why are YOU here?!
For all his posturing and preening,\nhis was but a trifling existence.
As are you, empty little princeling.
Defeat the Other and restore peace\nto the world. That was your naive plan\nall this time, was it not?
Beren, what have you done to Morsayati?
The Other's soul is at its most defenseless\nwhile being transferred to a new vessel.
The Other is no more—he has\nbeen absorbed into Beren.
Beren, how does it feel to have gained the\npower of the Other—the creature once so\nfeared by human and dragon alike?
It is not entirely objectionable. For with it,\nthere is no longer any need for me to\nreplenish mana.
Stop! You musn't use that power further!
You're that girl from before!\nThe Zethia-a-like!
I thought you lost all your power and\nwere destroyed in the Binding Ruins.\nHow are you back here now?
Ah, Zethia—or, more appropriately,\nthe Zethia from another world.
With Morsayati's power lost, it would\nappear you have once again found your\nway here. How deeply fascinating.
My brothers, you must relinquish that\npower. It is beyond humans to wield.
It is reasonable for you to fear\nthis power. However...
I am stronger. It is as simple as that.\nTo me, the power of the Other is merely\na tool to be wielded in my service.
You would claim strength enough to speak\nof the Other's power in such a fashion?
I realize your world saw its ruin at the\nhands of the Other's power, but fear\nis born from ignorance.
Thus did I decide to learn all I can about\nit. Now the Other's power is no longer\na subject of fear to us.
If you are so concerned, I propose a test.
You know the power of the Other, yes?\nThen perhaps it would convince you if I\nerase you from existence here and now.
Tch! Who are you to interfere with me?
I was told not to allow harm to the Auspex,\nthough perhaps he did not mean that\nPARTICULAR Auspex...
Looks like we have another guest.\nThough I don't know who it is.
If you know me not, you would do well\nto learn. I am Volk, fang of the fangless,\nand I will be taking the Auspex!
Volk, is it? A name I'll no doubt forget.\nIf you seek to interfere, you will meet\nyour end here.

Another little prince, eh? And one
with the power of the Other himself?
How very blessed you are...and
how IRREMISSIBLE!
Chosen by birth! Chosen for power!\nMerely by existing do all of you\npersecute the weak!

Strength is a sin, for it creates weakness!
Those who have it are unforgivable
sinners, for they create those who
have not!
Ain't ya got somethin' better to do than\nwaste our time with this nonsense?\nThe hell do ya even WANT?!
I am here to get it all back. You are false,\nyet blessed—and you seek to steal away\nthat which belongs to the true one!
Ah, yes. It all makes sense now.\nIf Agito has made an appearance,\nit means ＂he＂ is nearby as well.
Beren, let us now away; I do not\nbelieve this man to be our enemy.
It matters not. He seems to be acquainted\nwith our dear ＂younger brother,＂ so if you\ndesire it, he will likely show his face anon.
{player_name}, dear ＂brother...＂\nWhat you will face now is a truth\nand world you do not wish to see.
If you can endure what is to come,\nthen we shall meet again.
What are you talking about, Phares?
You must all help me pursue them—\nwe cannot permit Beren to wield\nthe Other's power as he pleases!
Do as you will—I'll not interfere.\nBut I WILL need you to leave\nthis world's Auspex here.
What are you going to do with our Zethia?
The Auspex must be returned to her\nrightful place.
If Zethia belongs anywhere, it's obviously\nwith {player_name}!
Do you truly think we went to all the\ntrouble of saving her just to let some\nother yodel steal her away again?!
I ask: Who is the true thief here,\nand who has he stolen FROM?!

The haves are always the thieves,
and the have-nots their victims!
You—and all people like you—
have stolen EVERYTHING!

I must reclaim what you have stolen from
the people who have not...and I must
reclaim the Auspex for the prince
from whom she was stolen!
We are Agito! Fangs of the fangless!\nKnow the resentment of those\nwho have lost all to your kind!
